Class MovieScreening

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.MovieScreening

  • public class MovieScreening

      • MovieScreening

                      java.util.Calendar startTime,
                      java.util.Calendar endTime,
                      MovieClassType movieType,
                      int cinemaID,
                      int movieID)
        Creates a new Movie Screening with its attributes. It will check based on this if the movie is available for booking.
        Parameters:
        movieScreeningID - Movie Screening ID of the movie screening.
        startTime - Starting time of the movie screening.
        endTime - End time of the movie screening.
        movieType - Type of the movie screening.
        cinemaID - CinemaID of the movie being screened at.
        movieID - MovieID of the movie being screened.

      • MovieScreening

        public MovieScreening​(int movieScreeningID,
                      java.util.Calendar startTime,
                      java.util.Calendar endTime,
                      MovieClassType movieType,
                      int cinemaID,
                      int movieID,
                      Seat[][] seats,
                      boolean isExpired)
        Creates a new Movie Screening with its attributes. This constructor is called by the loading of database.
        Parameters:
        movieScreeningID - Movie Screening ID of the movie screening.
        startTime - Starting time of the movie screening.
        endTime - End time of the movie screening.
        movieType - Class type of the movie being screened.
        cinemaID - CinemaID of the movie being screened at.
        movieID - MovieID of the movie being screened.
        seats - Seats of the movie that is available for booking
        isExpired - If the movie screening is still available for booking.
